  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some ways to call the US from Italy?",
  "response": "Calling the US from Italy can be done using several methods. Here are some options:\n\n1. **Landline or Mobile Phone**:\n   - **Dialing Directly**: You can call the US directly from an Italian landline or mobile phone. \n     - First, dial the international access code (00 in Italy).\n     - Next, dial the US country code (1).\n     - Finally, enter the area code and the local number. \n     - For example, to call a New York number (212-555-1234), you would dial: 00-1-212-555-1234.\n\n2. **VoIP Services**:\n   - Use Voice over Internet Protocol (VoIP) services like Skype, WhatsApp, Zoom, or Google Voice. These platforms allow you to make calls using the internet, often for free or at a lower cost.\n\n3. **Calling Cards**:\n   - Purchase an international calling card that offers calling to the US. These cards often provide cheaper rates, but be aware of any potential fees.\n\n4. **Mobile Apps**:\n   - Use mobile apps like Viber, FaceTime, or Facebook Messenger to make voice or video calls for free if you have a good internet connection.\n\n5. **Local SIM Card with International Plans**:\n   - If you're in Italy for an extended period, consider getting a local SIM card that includes international calling options to the US.\n\n6. **Calling from Hotels**:\n   - Many hotels provide services to make international calls. However, this can be quite pricey, so confirm the rates beforehand.\n\nWhen opting for any method, be sure to check the rates for international calls, as they can vary significantly based on your service provider or the service you choose.",
